JAEWON: Interest-free?

2092
01:06:16,576 --> 01:06:17,433
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Interest-free?

2093
01:06:17,433 --> 01:06:18,240
(What a funny student)

2094
01:06:18,400 --> 01:06:19,456
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Interest-free, interest-free?

2095
01:06:19,456 --> 01:06:20,320
NICHOLAS: Lump sum?

2096
01:06:21,344 --> 01:06:22,752
(Simple interest vs. compound interest)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: The answer is compound interest.

2097
01:06:22,752 --> 01:06:23,833
(The answer is compound interest)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Einstein called it

2098
01:06:24,160 --> 01:06:25,760
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: one of the eight wonders of the world,
- DANIEL: Oh, I don't know.

2099
01:06:25,984 --> 01:06:27,500
(Write it down for now)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: and humanity's greatest invention.

2100
01:06:27,500 --> 01:06:28,960
(Important point: Simple and compound interest)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: This is important, so let's go through it.

2101
01:06:28,960 --> 01:06:30,144
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Simple interest...

2102
01:06:30,533 --> 01:06:32,900
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Simple interest
is applied only to the principal.

2103
01:06:32,900 --> 01:06:34,112
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Say the principal is KRW 1 million.

2104
01:06:34,112 --> 01:06:35,392
(If the principal is KRW 1 million
and the interest is 10 percent)

2105
01:06:35,392 --> 01:06:37,216
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: The interest is simply 10 percent.

2106
01:06:37,376 --> 01:06:38,624
NICHOLAS: Then it's always 10 percent.

2107
01:06:38,624 --> 01:06:40,288
(The interest is KRW 100,000)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: That's right, KRW 100,000.

2108
01:06:41,566 --> 01:06:42,560
(After saving for 10 years,)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Since it's 10 percent,

2109
01:06:42,560 --> 01:06:43,296
(the interest remains KRW 100,000)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: it's another KRW 100,000, right?

2110
01:06:43,296 --> 01:06:43,866
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: So then...

2111
01:06:44,800 --> 01:06:47,000
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: interest income
of KRW 1 million is KRW 1 million.

2112
01:06:47,000 --> 01:06:49,300
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Since the principal
was KRW 1 million,

2113
01:06:49,664 --> 01:06:51,456
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: in 10 years,
you'll receive KRW 2 million.

2114
01:06:51,456 --> 01:06:51,936
(After saving for 10 years, salary of KRW 1 million
plus interest of KRW 1 million equals KRW 2 million)

2115
01:06:51,936 --> 01:06:52,576
DANIEL: Yes.

2116
01:06:52,966 --> 01:06:54,900
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: But with compound interest...

2117
01:06:54,900 --> 01:06:58,144
NICHOLAS: Compound interest adds
the earned interest to the principal.

2118
01:06:58,144 --> 01:06:58,800
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: That's right.

2119
01:06:58,800 --> 01:06:59,616
(Add 10 percent of interest
to KRW 1 million principal, KRW 1.1 million)

2120
01:06:59,616 --> 01:07:00,608
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's KRW 1.1 million.

2121
01:07:01,760 --> 01:07:02,432
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Right?

2122
01:07:03,168 --> 01:07:04,960
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Then from here,

2123
01:07:04,960 --> 01:07:07,616
(The next interest is 10 percent of KRW 1.1 million,
not the principal of KRW 1 million)

2124
01:07:07,616 --> 01:07:08,672
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: 10 percent of KRW 1.1 million

2125
01:07:09,248 --> 01:07:10,266
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: would be...

2126
01:07:10,464 --> 01:07:11,424
DANIEL: The interest is KRW 110,000.

2127
01:07:11,424 --> 01:07:12,128
TRAINEE: The interest is KRW 110,000.

2128
01:07:12,128 --> 01:07:12,672
DANIEL: The principal plus interest is KRW 1,210,000.

2129
01:07:12,672 --> 01:07:13,248
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: That's right.

2130
01:07:13,800 --> 01:07:14,784
(Compound interest is much more profitable than simple interest)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: KRW 1,210,000.

2131
01:07:14,784 --> 01:07:16,480
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: As it keeps going...

2132
01:07:17,233 --> 01:07:17,952
(As the complex calculations begin)

2133
01:07:17,952 --> 01:07:19,968
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: How much difference
will there be? For example...

2134
01:07:20,500 --> 01:07:23,400
(Mind getting foggy)

2135
01:07:23,400 --> 01:07:25,344
(Stretching for no reason)

2136
01:07:27,166 --> 01:07:29,466
(Writing to regain focus)

2137
01:07:32,633 --> 01:07:35,733
(Eyelids stubbornly growing heavier)

2138
01:07:35,936 --> 01:07:39,584
(Internal yawn)

2139
01:07:41,200 --> 01:07:44,333
(Same ordeal? Being experienced by same-age friends)

2140
01:07:47,904 --> 01:07:49,984
(Polite internal yawn)

2141
01:07:51,033 --> 01:07:52,733
(Moist eye contact)

2142
01:07:54,000 --> 01:07:56,928
(Older members losing their edge)

2143
01:07:58,666 --> 01:08:01,766
(Ace hanging on with mental strength)

2144
01:08:01,833 --> 01:08:03,266
(Example scenario)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I have KRW 1 billion!

2145
01:08:03,424 --> 01:08:04,352
HYUNJUN: Amazing!

2146
01:08:04,666 --> 01:08:06,466
