2147
01:08:06,466 --> 01:08:08,233
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Okay, shall we take a look at this?

2148
01:08:09,033 --> 01:08:11,400
(The teacher who came prepared with lesson materials)

2149
01:08:11,584 --> 01:08:12,896
HYUNJUN: Oh these numbers...

2150
01:08:12,896 --> 01:08:14,304
(Dizzying)

2151
01:08:14,304 --> 01:08:15,104
(Difference between simple and compound interest)

2152
01:08:15,104 --> 01:08:17,280
(All numbers)

2153
01:08:19,712 --> 01:08:21,666
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Shall we take a look?

2154
01:08:21,666 --> 01:08:23,264
JAEWON: Wow, too many zeros.

2155
01:08:23,520 --> 01:08:25,408
(Sleep has completely fled)

2156
01:08:25,728 --> 01:08:27,328
(Proceeding with lesson)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Let's say it's 100 million,

2157
01:08:27,328 --> 01:08:28,366
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: you have a principal of 100 million.

2158
01:08:28,366 --> 01:08:29,600
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: The interest is 10 percent.

2159
01:08:29,600 --> 01:08:30,336
(Brainpower fully engaged)

2160
01:08:30,336 --> 01:08:32,544
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: With simple interest,

2161
01:08:32,544 --> 01:08:33,920
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: going all the way down...

2162
01:08:33,920 --> 01:08:34,944
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: How much is it at the very bottom?

2163
01:08:34,944 --> 01:08:37,824
DANIEL: One, ten, hundred, thousand, ten thousand,
hundred thousand, million, ten million...

2164
01:08:37,824 --> 01:08:38,400
DANIEL: 400 million.

2165
01:08:38,400 --> 01:08:40,066
(With simple interest, it's 400 million)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's 400 million, 400 million.

2166
01:08:40,066 --> 01:08:41,966
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: But with compound interest,
how much?

2167
01:08:42,033 --> 01:08:43,232
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's 1.7 billion.

2168
01:08:43,584 --> 01:08:44,533
JAEWON: Wow.

2169
01:08:44,533 --> 01:08:46,066
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: When it comes to managing money,

2170
01:08:46,066 --> 01:08:48,633
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: understanding
compound interest is very important.

2171
01:08:49,766 --> 01:08:50,933
(Make sure to take notes)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: So, regarding money...

2172
01:08:50,933 --> 01:08:52,133
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Let's say you want to save.

2173
01:08:52,256 --> 01:08:53,888
(How you handle money matters)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Whether it's compound interest given once a year,

2174
01:08:54,048 --> 01:08:55,136
(Compound interest)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: or monthly compound interest,

2175
01:08:55,360 --> 01:08:56,736
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: or whether it's given monthly...

2176
01:08:56,736 --> 01:08:57,760
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It'll differ based on this.

2177
01:08:57,760 --> 01:08:58,720
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: By the way,

2178
01:08:59,968 --> 01:09:01,792
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: do you know the Rule of 72?

2179
01:09:02,016 --> 01:09:02,848
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Rule of 72?

2180
01:09:02,944 --> 01:09:03,904
DANIEL: I don't know.

2181
01:09:04,200 --> 01:09:05,966
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Just memorize it, it's useful.

2182
01:09:05,966 --> 01:09:07,200
HYUNJUN: Rule of 72, let's go!

2183
01:09:07,900 --> 01:09:10,033
(JAEWON, now awake, quickly takes notes)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: There's something called the Rule of 72.

2184
01:09:10,080 --> 01:09:11,776
DANIEL: I can sound smart somewhere with this!

2185
01:09:12,133 --> 01:09:13,866
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: The Rule of 72 shows

2186
01:09:13,866 --> 01:09:15,866
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: just how
important interest rates are.

2187
01:09:16,000 --> 01:09:17,216
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You have 72,

2188
01:09:17,216 --> 01:09:19,328
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: and you divide it
by the interest rate

2189
01:09:19,968 --> 01:09:21,266
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: we mentioned earlier.

2190
01:09:21,266 --> 01:09:23,533
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Now, if the interest rate
is 3 percent.

2191
01:09:23,533 --> 01:09:27,366
(Divide 72 by the interest rate of 3 percent)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: 72 divided by 3.

2192
01:09:27,456 --> 01:09:27,904
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: 24.

2193
01:09:27,904 --> 01:09:28,608
DANIEL: 24.

2194
01:09:29,248 --> 01:09:30,464
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Divide 72 by 6.

2195
01:09:30,464 --> 01:09:30,944
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: How much is it?

2196
01:09:30,944 --> 01:09:31,840
JAEWON: It's 12.

2197
01:09:31,968 --> 01:09:32,768
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: 12.

2198
01:09:33,600 --> 01:09:34,592
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Oh, it's good, it's good.

2199
01:09:34,592 --> 01:09:35,066
TRAINEE: Fast.

2200
01:09:35,066 --> 01:09:36,032
(Genuine gesture of concentration)

2201
01:09:36,032 --> 01:09:37,248
TRAINEE: Fast calculation.

2202
01:09:37,248 --> 01:09:38,176
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Divide 72...

2203
01:09:38,176 --> 01:09:39,104
(Brain at full power)

2204
01:09:39,104 --> 01:09:40,256
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: by 8, what's the answer?

2205
01:09:40,416 --> 01:09:40,832
HYUNJUN: 9.

2206
01:09:40,832 --> 01:09:41,633
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: 9, right.

2207
01:09:41,633 --> 01:09:42,966
(Answer given with deep breath)
TRAINEE: Ha ha ha.

2208
01:09:43,936 --> 01:09:44,704
(Saw that?)
DANIEL: He wants to get it right.

2209
01:09:44,800 --> 01:09:45,536
DANIEL: 9!

2210
01:09:45,536 --> 01:09:47,456
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: If you divide 72 by 12...

2211
01:09:47,616 --> 01:09:48,512
(Gold, Silver)
- DANIEL: 6. - JAEWON: It's 6.

2212
01:09:48,512 --> 01:09:49,376
(Bronze)
HYUNJUN: It's 6.

2213
01:09:49,376 --> 01:09:50,366
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Yes.

2214
01:09:50,366 --> 01:09:52,300
(The value divided by the interest rate)
What does this mean?

2215
01:09:52,300 --> 01:09:54,400
NICHOLAS: The higher the interest rate,

2216
01:09:54,400 --> 01:09:58,912
NICHOLAS: the time to earn the same amount decreases.

2217
01:09:59,168 --> 01:09:59,904
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: That's right.

2218
01:09:59,904 --> 01:10:00,448
DANIEL: Oh, time.

2219
01:10:00,448 --> 01:10:01,300
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Exactly.

2220
01:10:01,300 --> 01:10:02,866
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: For example, I have 100 million.

2221
01:10:03,966 --> 01:10:07,666
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I have 100 million,
and I want to make it 200 million.

2222
01:10:08,633 --> 01:10:10,233
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I want to double my assets.

2223
01:10:10,233 --> 01:10:11,800
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's the time it takes.

2224
01:10:12,896 --> 01:10:16,224
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: With 3 percent of interest,
it takes 24 years to double 100 million.

2225
01:10:16,352 --> 01:10:17,696
(To double an asset at 3 percent of interest,
it takes 24 years)

2226
01:10:17,760 --> 01:10:19,296
(Doubling assets at an interest rate of 12 percent takes 6 years)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: At 12 percent of interest, it takes six years.

2227
01:10:20,544 --> 01:10:21,333
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: So,

2228
01:10:21,333 --> 01:10:23,533
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: this is
the importance of interest rates.

2229
01:10:23,666 --> 01:10:24,600
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: So,

2230
01:10:24,600 --> 01:10:27,000
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: depending on
how much the interest rate is,

2231
01:10:27,000 --> 01:10:30,633
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: the speed
at which your assets grow changes.

2232
01:10:30,633 --> 01:10:32,666
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: What I want to say is...

2233
01:10:32,666 --> 01:10:35,000
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You're now
just starting in society, right?

2234
01:10:35,000 --> 01:10:36,666
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Therefore,
you need to manage your money.

2235
01:10:36,666 --> 01:10:38,866
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You should cut back
on things you can reduce in spending.

2236
01:10:38,866 --> 01:10:41,366
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Luxury items, designer goods...

2237
01:10:41,366 --> 01:10:43,333
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You can buy them later
after earning lots of money.

2238
01:10:43,333 --> 01:10:46,100
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You're young enough to be beautiful.

2239
01:10:46,100 --> 01:10:48,466
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You shine even without those things.
- HYUNJUN: Thank you.

2240
01:10:48,666 --> 01:10:50,752
(Idol routine)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I saw you dance earlier.

2241
01:10:50,784 --> 01:10:51,591
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's completely different.

2242
01:10:51,866 --> 01:10:54,133
