NA PD: encounter unexpected situations.

2263
01:11:37,472 --> 01:11:40,166
NA PD: What were we supposed to do this morning?

2264
01:11:40,166 --> 01:11:40,832
HAMIN: Swimming.

2265
01:11:40,832 --> 01:11:42,833
(The students had plans to go swimming this morning)
NA PD: We planned to swim, but why couldn't you go?

2266
01:11:42,880 --> 01:11:44,160
(Swimming was canceled due to rain)
WOOLIN: Because it rained.

2267
01:11:44,768 --> 01:11:47,400
NA PD: These things happen, right?

2268
01:11:47,400 --> 01:11:48,640
NA PD: Suddenly.

2269
01:11:48,640 --> 01:11:50,240
(Outdoor filming always involves variables)
NA PD: This is something you couldn't predict.

2270
01:11:50,461 --> 01:11:51,584
NA PD: But this part...

2271
01:11:51,584 --> 01:11:53,664
(Changed schedule)
NA PD: In the past, we edited and removed it.

2272
01:11:55,200 --> 01:11:59,233
NA PD: But when filming '2 Days & 1 Night',
such things happened too often.

2273
01:11:59,566 --> 01:12:01,633
NA PD: It felt like a waste
just to edit it, and secondly,

2274
01:12:01,633 --> 01:12:03,456
NA PD: the members' reactions were so funny.

2275
01:12:04,257 --> 01:12:05,200
NA PD: For example,

2276
01:12:05,200 --> 01:12:07,633
(For example, if we couldn't go to a planned trip)
NA PD: if a sudden downpour ruined our planned trip,

2277
01:12:07,766 --> 01:12:10,400
NA PD: they'd say, "Ugh, what is this? So annoying!"

2278
01:12:10,400 --> 01:12:12,160
NA PD: But that was so funny!

2279
01:12:12,544 --> 01:12:15,066
NA PD: So, to make

2280
01:12:15,066 --> 01:12:17,666
NA PD: the sudden events fun somehow...

2281
01:12:17,900 --> 01:12:20,166
(Started appearing to explain situations)
NA PD: That's when I first started appearing.

2282
01:12:21,888 --> 01:12:25,248
(To a somewhat dissatisfied cast)
NA PD: Let's play soccer before the sun sets today!

2283
01:12:25,824 --> 01:12:28,064
(Specialist in enticing proposals)
KANG HO DONG: One, two, three, deal!

2284
01:12:29,366 --> 01:12:31,700
(Note: The type that loses out)

2285
01:12:31,700 --> 01:12:35,232
(Scene of PD negotiating with cast)
NA PD: I kept negotiating,

2286
01:12:35,766 --> 01:12:39,066
NA PD: so the viewers found it entertaining!

2287
01:12:39,066 --> 01:12:40,933
NA PD: So gradually,

2288
01:12:40,933 --> 01:12:43,266
NA PD: my appearances increased!

2289
01:12:43,360 --> 01:12:47,533
(Story of becoming a YouTuber with 7 million followers)
NA PD: I started appearing a lot on TV.

2290
01:12:47,808 --> 01:12:52,066
NA PD: In Korean variety shows,
one of the very important things is...

2291
01:12:52,266 --> 01:12:54,048
(Difference from foreign variety shows)
NA PD: The difference between foreign variety shows

2292
01:12:54,048 --> 01:12:55,300
NA PD: and Korean ones is that

2293
01:12:56,333 --> 01:12:58,366
NA PD: in Korea, they value reality a lot.

2294
01:12:59,712 --> 01:13:01,466
NA PD: And Korean viewers

2295
01:13:01,466 --> 01:13:04,033
NA PD: also find sudden real-life events
and unexpected situations

2296
01:13:04,233 --> 01:13:05,504
NA PD: really funny!

2297
01:13:06,000 --> 01:13:06,944
NA PD: Do you know why?

2298
01:13:07,680 --> 01:13:08,800
NA PD: Because you get to see

2299
01:13:08,800 --> 01:13:11,552
NA PD: their true selves at that moment.

2300
01:13:11,680 --> 01:13:14,100
NA PD: In a reality setting,

2301
01:13:14,366 --> 01:13:17,700
NA PD: when a character suddenly appears,

2302
01:13:18,033 --> 01:13:20,466
(Situation with sudden unexpected variables!)
NA PD: it's an unexpected twist.

2303
01:13:20,466 --> 01:13:22,560
NA PD: As you overcome those obstacles,

2304
01:13:22,900 --> 01:13:27,600
NA PD: you're showing viewers your positive strength.

2305
01:13:27,600 --> 01:13:31,666
NA PD: In Korean variety shows,
that's extremely important!

2306
01:13:31,666 --> 01:13:33,312
NA PD: I don't know about other countries, though.

2307
01:13:33,966 --> 01:13:35,266
NA PD: So, with this as a conclusion!

2308
01:13:35,266 --> 01:13:38,100
(Ending the variety show class)
NA PD: Let's wrap up the class about variety shows.

2309
01:13:38,419 --> 01:13:41,184
ALL: Thank you.

2310
01:13:41,376 --> 01:13:42,752
NA PD: We'll meet after you debut!

2311
01:13:42,752 --> 01:13:43,840
ALL: Yes, thank you.

2312
01:13:43,996 --> 01:13:44,832
(Restless)
NA PD: Fighting, fighting!

2313
01:13:44,832 --> 01:13:45,568
TRAINEE: Thank you.

2314
01:13:45,568 --> 01:13:46,816
HAMIN: Um...

2315
01:13:47,168 --> 01:13:48,384
HAMIN: could I get an autograph?

2316
01:13:48,602 --> 01:13:49,632
NA PD: Oh, of course, of course.

2317
01:13:49,632 --> 01:13:51,680
CHARLIE: Oh, me too!

2318
01:13:51,840 --> 01:13:52,576
WOOLIN: Me too, me too!

2319
01:13:52,736 --> 01:13:53,248
KACHIN: Me, me!

2320
01:13:53,440 --> 01:13:56,200
NA PD: Hey, isn't this supposed to be
for you guys to do for me?

2321
01:13:56,200 --> 01:13:57,408
WOOLIN: Line up, line up.

2322
01:13:57,408 --> 01:13:58,400
NA PD: Okay.

2323
01:13:58,784 --> 01:14:00,448
CHARLIE: Hehe! Hehehe!

2324
01:14:00,448 --> 01:14:01,440
(Very excited fans)

2325
01:14:02,966 --> 01:14:04,448
(HAMIN, who boldly asked for a signature, came in first)
HAMIN: Thank you.

2326
01:14:04,512 --> 01:14:05,568
- NA PD: CHARLIE!
- CHARLIE: Yes.

2327
01:14:06,464 --> 01:14:08,576
(Certified)

2328
01:14:10,391 --> 01:14:11,104
(Haha!)

2329
01:14:11,296 --> 01:14:12,384
KACHIN: Oh, yes, thank you.

2330
01:14:12,576 --> 01:14:13,824
WOOLIN: Just on my clothes.

2331
01:14:14,176 --> 01:14:15,433
NA PD: Hey, will it be okay?

2332
01:14:15,600 --> 01:14:16,576
WOOLIN: It's fine, I really like it.

2333
01:14:16,576 --> 01:14:18,432
NA PD: Shouldn't you get
permission from your teacher?

2334
01:14:18,432 --> 01:14:19,648
- WOOLIN: Ah, it's okay.
- NA PD: Alright, then.

2335
01:14:19,966 --> 01:14:22,300
(Reform carried out without Teachers' Office approval)
WOOLIN: You're the teacher.

2336
01:14:22,304 --> 01:14:23,392
SADAHARU: Me too, me too.

2337
01:14:23,872 --> 01:14:25,440
(Already spread out the T-shirt and waiting)

2338
01:14:25,440 --> 01:14:26,336
WOOLIN: Please do it.

2339
01:14:31,584 --> 01:14:33,933
(An unforgettable souvenir
for 'New Journey to the West' Kids)

2340
01:14:35,200 --> 01:14:36,900
(One last commemorative photo)
ALL: Thank you.

2341
01:14:37,333 --> 01:14:38,866
(Time to say goodbye)
- ALL: Thank you. - NA PD: Hey, really...

2342
01:14:39,033 --> 01:14:40,960
- NA PD: do well and debut successfully.
- ALL: Thank you.

2343
01:14:40,960 --> 01:14:42,016
NA PD: After becoming a star,

2344
01:14:42,112 --> 01:14:42,912
NA PD: don't forget me.

2345
01:14:44,288 --> 01:14:45,696
- WOOLIN: Please don't forget us.
- HAMIN: Thank you.

2346
01:14:45,838 --> 01:14:46,560
NA PD: Don't forget me after becoming a star.

2347
01:14:46,784 --> 01:14:47,333
ALL: Thank you.

2348
01:14:47,333 --> 01:14:50,016
(Promise to meet again, the variety show lesson ends)
ALL: Bye, take care.

2349
01:14:51,233 --> 01:14:53,733
STAFF: It seems the class next door has ended.

2350
01:14:53,766 --> 01:14:55,168
(Economics teacher still has class content left)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: There's one last thing

2351
01:14:55,168 --> 01:14:56,400
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I wanted to tell you all, okay?

2352
01:14:56,480 --> 01:14:57,824
HYUNJUN: Yes, please.

2353
01:14:57,966 --> 01:15:00,400
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: From now on,
the more you live the idol life

2354
01:15:00,400 --> 01:15:01,933
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: and gain popularity,

2355
01:15:01,933 --> 01:15:04,166
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: the more contracts
you'll have to sign.

2356
01:15:04,352 --> 01:15:05,888
(Lecture on contract writing)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I wanted to teach you

2357
01:15:05,888 --> 01:15:07,616
(for WOOJEONG HIGH SCHOOL students)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: how to sign contracts,

2358
01:15:08,096 --> 01:15:09,728
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: but it feels a bit disappointing

2359
01:15:10,020 --> 01:15:11,680
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: to leave without doing that...

2360
01:15:11,904 --> 01:15:15,328
- NICHOLAS: We're fine, even if we're here longer...
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Yeah?

2361
01:15:15,936 --> 01:15:16,960
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: This is a contract.

2362
01:15:18,112 --> 01:15:19,766
(Distributing prepared contracts)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: This is a contract.

2363
01:15:20,004 --> 01:15:20,896
DANIEL: Oh, is it a real contract?

2364
01:15:21,216 --> 01:15:22,720
(Actual standard contract form used)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Yes, this is a real contract,

2365
01:15:22,720 --> 01:15:25,760
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: a standard form
provided by the government.

2366
01:15:27,066 --> 01:15:30,100
(At the same time, a line for economics
teacher's autographs forms)

2367
01:15:30,100 --> 01:15:31,466
SADAHARU: Do you know who this is?

2368
01:15:31,466 --> 01:15:32,384
CHARLIE: I know!

2369
01:15:32,768 --> 01:15:34,208
CHARLIE: King is Coming.

2370
01:15:34,272 --> 01:15:34,976
WOOLIN: Egg King!

2371
01:15:35,136 --> 01:15:36,128
(Egg King explaining the contract)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: It's a standard contract

2372
01:15:36,128 --> 01:15:38,000
CEO KO JOONG SEOK:prepared by the government.

2373
01:15:38,000 --> 01:15:39,840
(Peeking)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: If you look at page 2 here...

2374
01:15:40,000 --> 01:15:41,504
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Do you guys
know how to read contracts?

2375
01:15:41,920 --> 01:15:43,520
HAMIN: They are actually taking a class.

2376
01:15:43,520 --> 01:15:44,652
WOOLIN: They are too serious right now.

2377
01:15:44,736 --> 01:15:46,464
(Because we're having a serious talk)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You know you shouldn't sign recklessly, right?

2378
01:15:46,464 --> 01:15:47,744
- ALL: Yes.
- NA PD: Okay.

2379
01:15:47,744 --> 01:15:50,592
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You should never
sign a contract if you don't understand it.

2380
01:15:51,933 --> 01:15:53,613
(What to look out for in contract clauses)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: When you look at contracts,

2381
01:15:53,613 --> 01:15:54,533
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: what you should look for is...

2382
01:15:54,816 --> 01:15:57,633
(Specifically 'Rights and obligations')
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You need to find the rights and obligations.

2383
01:15:57,664 --> 01:15:59,008
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: You must
pay attention to these things.

2384
01:15:59,200 --> 01:16:01,366
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: When reading a contract,
always check your own rights and obligations.

2385
01:16:01,366 --> 01:16:04,266
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Also look for what rights
and obligations the other party has.

2386
01:16:04,384 --> 01:16:06,016
(Advice he wanted to give to young novices)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Examine it carefully,

2387
01:16:06,240 --> 01:16:09,833
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: and revise
or modify it in your favor.

2388
01:16:09,833 --> 01:16:12,966
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Once you fully understand,
that's when you sign.

2389
01:16:13,056 --> 01:16:14,784
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Got it?
- ALL: Yep!

2390
01:16:15,616 --> 01:16:16,992
(End of economics class)
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: That's all for today.

2391
01:16:16,992 --> 01:16:18,400
ALL: Thank you.

2392
01:16:18,560 --> 01:16:20,352
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Yes, well done everyone.

2393
01:16:20,352 --> 01:16:22,433
(Applause for the teacher who taught with sincerity)

2394
01:16:22,693 --> 01:16:23,936
- HYUNJUN: Become rich.
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Okay.

2395
01:16:24,300 --> 01:16:26,700
NICHOLAS: Have you given lectures like this before?

2396
01:16:26,700 --> 01:16:28,100
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: No, this is my first time as well.

2397
01:16:28,100 --> 01:16:29,800
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: So I studied a lot to prepare.

2398
01:16:29,800 --> 01:16:32,533
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I read about
ten books to get ready to come here.

2399
01:16:32,533 --> 01:16:34,368
(The teacher who studied for a month,
reading ten books for the class)

2400
01:16:34,464 --> 01:16:38,368
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: But I think I only
conveyed about half of what I studied.

2401
01:16:39,110 --> 01:16:40,256
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Anyway, everyone,

2402
01:16:40,512 --> 01:16:43,533
- CEO KO JOONG SEOK: I hope everything goes well for you.
- ALL: Thank you.

2403
01:16:43,872 --> 01:16:45,280
(Waiting line to greet Egg King)

2404
01:16:49,133 --> 01:16:50,496
(Greeting Egg King on his way home)
ALL: Hello.

2405
01:16:50,496 --> 01:16:51,328
WOOLIN: Please sign for me.

2406
01:16:51,900 --> 01:16:53,600
(Fan signing event on the way home)

2407
01:16:53,600 --> 01:16:54,513
WOOLIN: It's an honor.

2408
01:16:55,360 --> 01:16:56,100
CEO KO JOONG SEOK: Done.

2409
01:16:56,100 --> 01:16:58,600
TRAINEE: Thank you.

2410
01:17:00,533 --> 01:17:02,533
(Showing off autographs)

2411
01:17:03,166 --> 01:17:05,733
(A commemorative photo is a must)

2412
01:17:06,333 --> 01:17:10,100
(Thanks to CEO KO JOONG SEOK for coming all this way)

2413
01:17:10,359 --> 01:17:13,376
ALL: Thank you.

2414
01:17:13,376 --> 01:17:14,592
(Really leaving)
TRAINEE: Thank you.

2415
01:17:14,944 --> 01:17:16,096
JAEWON: It was a useful class.

2416
01:17:16,666 --> 01:17:18,688
(Fan love class is also nearing its end)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Now, we've wrapped

2417
01:17:18,688 --> 01:17:19,766
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: the fan cup like this.

2418
01:17:20,033 --> 01:17:21,504
(Wrap-up with a fan love quiz)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: I'll wrap up the class

2419
01:17:21,504 --> 01:17:23,033
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: with a simple activity.

2420
01:17:23,233 --> 01:17:25,066
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Those who answer correctly,

2421
01:17:25,066 --> 01:17:26,496
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: you'll get

2422
01:17:26,496 --> 01:17:28,366
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: a 5,000 won coupon.

2423
01:17:28,366 --> 01:17:30,016
(Monetary prize is involved)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: I'll give one for each correct answer.

2424
01:17:30,266 --> 01:17:32,066
- FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Try your best to get it right.
- TRAINEE: Okay.

2425
01:17:32,166 --> 01:17:33,333
HANBI: Let's go, let's go!

2426
01:17:33,856 --> 01:17:35,360
(First question)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Here is the first question.

2427
01:17:35,902 --> 01:17:36,704
(Left block, right block,
center block, gulbi seat)

2428
01:17:36,832 --> 01:17:39,712
(What does it mean?)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Raise your hand if you know the answer.

2429
01:17:43,066 --> 01:17:45,133
(I don't know)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Breathe, please.

2430
01:17:45,133 --> 01:17:46,304
(Left block, right block,
center block, gulbi seat)

2431
01:17:46,304 --> 01:17:48,066
KASSHO: Right block? Center block?

2432
01:17:48,333 --> 01:17:49,856
(Hint: Concert hall)
HANBI: This is a concert hall first of all.

2433
01:17:50,134 --> 01:17:51,168
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Correct, it's a concert.

2434
01:17:51,610 --> 01:17:52,128
(Realized)
HANBI: Left block.

2435
01:17:52,900 --> 01:17:56,128
HANBI: Left block, right block,
center block, gulbi seat!

2436
01:17:56,224 --> 01:17:58,816
(Fish appears suddenly)
HANBI: Gulbi, what's gulbi?

2437
01:17:59,033 --> 01:18:01,533
HANBI: Gulbi hangs like this, right?

2438
01:18:02,100 --> 01:18:03,860
(For reference, fans evaluate gulbi seats like this)

2439
01:18:03,860 --> 01:18:06,500
(It's okay to be a gulbi stuck to the ceiling,
so please release the gulbi seats)

2440
01:18:06,912 --> 01:18:07,904
HANBI: Second floor? Second floor seats?

2441
01:18:07,904 --> 01:18:08,416
HANBI: No, it isn't.

2442
01:18:09,000 --> 01:18:10,272
(The second floor seats are more like tilefish than gulbi)
HANBI: Gulbi.

2443
01:18:11,808 --> 01:18:12,640
HARUTA: VIP.

2444
01:18:13,700 --> 01:18:17,800
(VIP seats are like premium seats)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: VIP is like gulbi... It's a really good spot.

2445
01:18:17,800 --> 01:18:19,104
SONGHA: SONGHA!

2446
01:18:19,264 --> 01:18:21,952
SONGHA: Left block, right block, center block.

2447
01:18:22,533 --> 01:18:23,584
SONGHA: Standing seats?

2448
01:18:23,584 --> 01:18:25,900
(Hey, is it hanging?)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Is the person standing the gulbi?

2449
01:18:25,900 --> 01:18:27,552
(Like hanging gulbi fish)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Gulbi fish are like this...

2450
01:18:27,552 --> 01:18:28,128
HANBI: The one hanging.

2451
01:18:28,800 --> 01:18:30,976
(A saying: 'It's okay even with this appearance.')
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Tied to a rope and hanging from the ceiling, right?

2452
01:18:30,976 --> 01:18:32,064
SONGHA: Like this.

2453
01:18:33,120 --> 01:18:35,552
(Much like this)

2454
01:18:35,872 --> 01:18:38,304
(Still happy)

2455
01:18:38,720 --> 01:18:40,352
(Hint: Gocheok Sky Dome)
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Think of Gocheok Sky Dome.

2456
01:18:40,352 --> 01:18:40,960
KASSHO: Gocheok Sky Dome?

2457
01:18:41,100 --> 01:18:41,792
HANBI: HANBI!

2458
01:18:42,300 --> 01:18:44,433
HANBI: Left block, right block, center block, and...

2459
01:18:44,433 --> 01:18:45,480
HANBI: the block right on the ceiling.

2460
01:18:45,984 --> 01:18:47,584
- FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: Correct.
- HANBI: Yay!

2461
01:18:48,000 --> 01:18:49,632
(Gulbi seat: A high-up seat with a "heaven view")

2462
01:18:49,632 --> 01:18:50,784
KASSHO: Fast.

2463
01:18:50,784 --> 01:18:53,984
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: When fans say
'Gocheok Sky Dome Gulbi Seat', they mean...

2464
01:18:54,080 --> 01:18:55,840
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: It's like watching a show
from the top of Gocheok Sky Dome.

2465
01:18:55,840 --> 01:18:59,360
(Hanging from the ceiling like a gulbi fish)

2466
01:18:59,360 --> 01:19:00,736
(Even like that, the hope of fans wishing to
have their own spots at the concert venue)

2467
01:19:00,761 --> 01:19:01,696
KASSHO: Gulbi seat.

2468
01:19:02,944 --> 01:19:03,968
(5,000 won culture gift coupon awarded)
HANBI: Thank you.

2469
01:19:05,166 --> 01:19:06,600
(Next question)
('Stanning with happiness')

2470
01:19:06,848 --> 01:19:09,024
JUSTIN: Sausage rice cake skewers?

2471
01:19:09,566 --> 01:19:11,566
(Sausage rice cake skewers...
a wrong answer leading to a rest area)

2472
01:19:12,416 --> 01:19:14,433
(Fans' expressions are hard to understand)

2473
01:19:15,233 --> 01:19:16,966
HANBI: Uh... what does 'eo' mean?

2474
01:19:18,080 --> 01:19:19,424
SONGHA: Ah, SONGHA!

2475
01:19:19,424 --> 01:19:20,096
FAN LOVE INSTRUCTOR: SONGHA.

2476
01:19:20,096 --> 01:19:23,488
SONGHA: 'Since we're going to
